inn1.comm: pitches outside leg stump and angles into Hayden's pads, flicked down to fine leg for one and Hayden's off the mark
on the pads again, defended to short midwicket

Hinds misses a plumb run-out chance! Straighter line on middle and off stump, Katich dabbed it past the bowler and set off for the single, Hinds runs in from mid-off and misses the under arm throw from about three yards
left alone outside off stump
cracker of a ball, pitches just outside off stump and nips back into Hayden who lets it go over the top of off stump
defended back to the bowler
pitches short of a length outside off atump and angles into Katich, defended on the back foot on the leg side
short of a length again, outside off stump, forced off the back foot past point
good length on off stump and nips back in to hit the pad, leg bye taken as the ball rolls on the off side
full and angling into the pads, flicked straight to square leg
that bounced a bit more from short of a length and moved away as well, Katich tries to cut but misses
fuller in length, Katich turns it off his pads to midwicket
full in length and on off stump, Hayden gets forward and punches it to mid-off
just a touch short and moving across Hayden from leg stump, cut to point
on the pads this time, Hayden plays it to short midwicket
outside off stump, Hayden drives off the back foot to cover
pitches outside leg stump and drifts down leg, that bounced very high and Baugh had to collect it above his head, wide called
pitches wide outside off stump and moves away, Hayden lets it go
full outside off stump, Hayden gets forward and drives hard, cover dives across and does well to stop it from going past him
pitches on off stump and moves away from Hayden, he lunges forward and drives without getting to the pitch of the ball, he gets a thick outside edge but it falls short of Gayle at first slip
nips back in off a short length and hits him on the thigh
touch shorter in length, Hayden takes two steps down the track and punches it down the ground for one
that's the first four of the innings, pitches outside off stump and moves away, Katich plays away from his boday and gets a thickish outside edge down to the third man boundary
defended back to the bowler
full on off stump from over the wicket, Hayden drives on the front foot to mid-off
short of a length and angling across Hayden who dabs it short of point for a sharp single. Cries of 'walk in fellas' are picked up on the stump microphone
full outside off stump, Katich gets forward and drives through the line past mid-off for four
poor ball, a half-volley on leg stump and Katich promptly flicks it for four through midwicket
defended on the back foot to cover
short of a length outside off stump, defended to point
pitches outside off stump and angles into off and middle stump, Hayden has no room to work with and defends it back to the bowler
on a good length in the channel outside off stump, moves a touch away from Hayden who watches it go past
drifting down leg side this time, Hayden tries to whip it off his pads but doesn't make contact
short of a length and on the pads again, turned off his hips for one
short and wide outside off stump, Katich moves towards it and cuts hard past point and to the fence, Katich all of a sudden has hit four boundaries
drifts down leg side, clips the pad on the way through to Baugh
defended to cover off the back foot, that angled across Hayden after pitching on leg and middle
short of a length on off stump, played off the back foot on the off side
fuller in length and on off stump, Hayden waits for it and drives down the ground. Cries of 'wait' but the ball doesn't beat mid-off
left alone perilously close to off stump, that nipped back into Hayden after pitching  just outside off stump

that nips back into Hayden again and he gets hit on the pad, there's a shout for lbw but Hayden was too far down the pitch, the ball deflects off the pad on the off side there could have been a run-out had the throw hit the stumps
wide outside off stump, the batsman frees his arms and slaps it over cover for four
defended on the off side
drifts on to the pads, worked off his hips using the bowler's pace down to fine leg
short of a length outside off stump, Hayden takes two steps down and muscles it over wide mid-on for four
defended on the leg side
pushed on the off side on the back foot
short of a length and drifting on to the pads, worked past square leg for two, there's a direct hit at the non-strikers end but the batsman's safe
short of a length outside off stump, pushed wide off cover for a single
pitching just outside leg stump and hits Hayden on the pad, that didn't bounce as high as one might have expected
another one keeps low, pitches on middle and angles across Hayden who defends on the back foot
played with an open face to point
short of a length on off stump, punched to mid-off for a quick single
defended back to the bowler
slower through the air on leg stump, Hayden makes room and steps down, he alomst yorks himself and digs it out to cover
played to mid-on for one

run-out! Katich gives himself room and drives trhough extra cover, the batsmen run an easy two but Katich wants the third, he charges back but Hayden isn't going anywhere, the throw comes to the wicketkeeper and Katich is stranded, Bradshaw was the fielder in the deep
defended back to the bowler
a touch shorter and Watson pulls it but can't beat midwicket
good length on off stump, Hayden attempts the drive but gets more of a thick inside edge to mid-on for one
in the channel outside off stump, Watson goes forward and defends but was late on it, the ball beats the bat
defended back to the bowler on the back foot
driven to mid off
short of a length outside off stump, Watson tries to force it through the off side on the back foot but hits it straight to Lara at cover.
drifting down leg side, played off his pads down to fine leg and Symonds is away
defended on the front foot on the off side
pitches outside off stump and angles away from Symonds who lets it go
pitches outside leg stump and holds its line down leg side, no wide called so that might have brushed Symonds on its way through
wide outside off stump, Symonds doesn't time it well and hits it to point
wide outside off stump, Symonds flashes hard and the ball flies down to third man for four
short of a length on the pads, played off his pads to square leg
full on leg and middle, driven to mid-on off the front foot

four, but so nearly caught! Banged in short and Hayden pulls it but gets more of a top edge, Bravo charges in off the square leg fence and dives spectacularly forward but the ball bounces just in front off him and goes for four
flicked off the pads for one
full and straight, played back to the bowler
short of a length on off stump and moves a shade away from Symonds who fends at it but gets beaten
wide outside off stump this time and moves away, Symonds lets it go
short of a length outside off stump, Hayden drives at it but gets beaten
angling into Hayden from outside off stump, the batsman gets hit on the pads

nearly another run-out, Hayden dabs it on the off side and Symonds sets off from the non-strikers endHayden sends him back, Bradshaw picks it up, turns and throws but doesn't hit the stumps or Symonds would have been out
defended on the leg side
driven straight down the ground but not well timed
fullish length on leg stump, defended to midwicket
a touch shorter outside off stump, it bounces a bit extra as well, Symonds tries to cut but doesn't time it well
defended off the back foot on the leg side
short of a length and angling into the pads, defended to midwicket
short of a length outside off stump, cut straight to point
played down to third man for one
on the hips, tucked away past square-leg and they run two.
Outside the off stump, left alone.

got him! West Indies get their reward for some tight bowling. The usual Bradshaw delivery - on a length, slanting away and offering no room. Symonds tried to make something happen. Slided back and tried to slash past point but only warmed Dwayne Smith's palms.
around the off and middle stump line, Clarke presents the full face of the bat in defense
another dot ball as Clarke, obviously, wants to play himself in. He has been in a good form here at Kuala Lumpur.
fullish, almost a yorker, squeezed past square-leg
bit of width outside the off stump, full in length, but Clarke decides to let it sail through to the wicketkeeper
around the offstump line, and the typical ODI shot, where the batsman opens the face of the blade and runs it down to third-man region.
slightly short in length, and just outside the off stump, Hayden thought he could cut it behind point, he should have but found the man at point.
Hayden cuts loose. He thrusts his front foot out, and hits through the line and the ball sails over mid-on
slanting across, Clarke thrusts his left foot out, covers his stumps and shoulders arms
almost beaten. I say almost as Clarke just about withdraws the bat at the last minute, little late in doing so and the ball whizzes past the hanging blade.
the second wide of the innings, down the leg side.  Not bad, considering West Indies were quite generous with the sundries in their first match.

Clarke returns to the hut. Slightly short of length, outside the off stump.  The length and the line tempted Clarke to break free. He tried - threw his bat at it, hoping the ball would sail past point, instead, it took the outside edge and flew straight to the lone slip fielder. And West Indies go into the celerbratory huddle.
outside the off stump and left alone.
Smith continues with his parsimonious offerings. Another one, on the stumps, offering neither length nor line to hit and patted back to him.
on the leg and middle, tries to flick it away, runs off the pads to shortish fine-leg
Hussey gets off the mark quietly with a nudge to third-man
hmmm...  Hayden tries to counterattack. runs down the track but doesnt find the length for it, gets an inside-edge which takes the ball to shortish fine-leg
Hussey does what Hayden wanted to do without any fuss. A fullish delivery on the middle and leg, and he leans forward and eases it, nonchalantly, past square-leg
outside the off stump but Hussey is not in a greedy mood, shoulders arms
Fullish delivery outside the off stump, Hayden comes forward, sees the room and decides to take toll. Threw his bat at it and a slash over point results.
a length-delivery, coming in slightly from the off stump, Hayden is again on his front foot, and pushes it back down the track
same line and length but slightly slower this time, gives time to Hayden to work it away to the on side, past square-leg
beaten! landed just outside the off stump and held its line, Hussey ended up pushing inside the line and the ball rolls along the ground enroute to the wicketkeeper
length-delivery on the off stump, pushed to covers
on the legs, worked to the square-leg area.
a length-delivery on the middle and leg, punched down the ground.
again on that leg and middle line, Hayden goes back and turns it towards square-leg
hits the off stump line, tickled to backward point
pushed to cover
Hayden decides to impose himself.  Walks down the track, plays a pick-up shot over the bowler's head but there is a long-on in place and he just gets a run
overpitched on the legs, turned behind square-leg and they run hard to take two
fullish one , just outside the off stump, Hussey eases forward, lets the ball come to him, opens the blade and runs it down to the third-man region
another length-delivery, on the middle and leg, and Hayden stays back, opens himself slightly and pushes the ball past the mid-on
fullish, right up there, on the middle and leg, turned straight to square-leg
floated on the middle and leg stump line, Hayden goes back, turns it past square-leg
again on that same line, this time Hussey pushes it down the ground, to long-on
hit back to the bowler, Samuels jumps to his right to make the stop
floated up slowly, on the leg and middle stump line, Hayden is on his front foot, waits, and drives it towards long-on
fullish, outside the off stump, Hussey reaches out for it, drives past cover
short of length, on the leg and middle line, Hussey stands up tall, works it behind square-leg

short of length, angling away and it came slow off the track, catching Hayden by surprise. he was ready with his forcing shot but was made to wait and in the end gets an inside-edge and they cross over for a single.
delivered from round the sticks. fullish, on the middle and leg. It keeps slightly low , hussey attempts to flick, misses and it runs off the pads
pushed past point
wide down the leg side. Bravo is bowling froun the around the wickets and he ended up pushing it little too much
length-delivery on the off stump line, Hussey gets on to the front foot, pushes it past cover
short and outside the off stump, cut past point.
one slip is in place. shortish delivery outside the off stump, forced past point
tries to cut past cover, doesn't quite find his timing, runs straight to cover
fullish on the legs, turned down to fine-leg
on the off stump line, swatted away to mid-off
The 100 is up. outside the off stump, Hayden goes back and across, gets close to the line and cuts past point
lands on the off stump line, turns away, Hayden is again back and across, cuts but the timing is not there and ends up swatting it to cover
fullish, from round the wickets, square-driven past point. Hussey always looks to get on his front foot
fullish delivery, on the off stump line, Hayden doesn't quite press forward, just pushes it on the up, down the ground
slower ball, floating in from outside the off stump, pushed to cover.
bit of width outside the off stump, Hussey steers it to the third-man region

Soft dismissal. What a way to go. The start smacked off arrogance and promised much but ....  Hayden just walked forward and across, Bravo held the length back, Hayden adjusted, swivelled and when you thought a big pull shot is going to be unfurled, he ends up patting it straight to the short fine-leg fielder, the only man in that arc.
gives the new batsman a slower ball striaght-up. Dips just outside the off stump, pushed to cover
outside the off stump, swatted away to backward point

oh ho! Lara, at backward point, was caught out! He started to move to his left as Hussey cut one his way, but the ball headed towards his right and Lara was left rooted at his position and was a mute witness to the boundary
driven to sweeper cover
floated up on the off stump line, outside in fact, Hussey decides to go for a sweep, misses and the ball thuds into the pads. Outside the line, though.
Samules continues with his miserly offerings.
spearing in late, fullish in length, Haddin gets his bat down in time, behind the line and pushes it towards mid-wicket
fullish, right up there, on the middle and off stump line, dug back to the bowler

hurled across full in length, just outside the off stump, Haddin attempts to drive it forcefully but doesn't find the timing and hence doesn't get much power behind the stroke and the ball rolls to cover
on the middle and leg, turned towards midwicket
similar ball, worked to midwicket

Ah! that slower ball is out again. Released between his thumb and fore-finger the ball loops out towards off and middle stump line, dips at the last moment, Haddin  spots it, and dead-bats it back down the track
Dwayne Smith starts his new spell with a beauty. A length delivery on the middle and off stump line,that moved late, past the defensive blade of Hussey.
fullish but this one is on the legs, pushed gently to the right of midwicket and they jog through for a single
slightly short in length, outside the off stump, Haddin pushes at it, bat hanging away from his body, and the ball rolls towards point
leans forward to a fullish delivery, pats it towards mid-off, who is standing deep, and they hurry through for a single.
eases forward to a length-delivery, pushes it to sweeper cover
overpitched on the legs, turned past square-leg.

Aha! another lovely slower ball, loops and dips in front of off stump, Haddin, who is standing outside his crease, just about to get his bat down in time, gets an outside-edge which takes the ball past point
fullish on the offstump line, driven to right of mid-off
on the legs, tucked past square-leg
outside the off stump, left alone
drifting down the legside and Hussey waits for the ball to arrive, gets inside the line and tickles it fine to the fine-leg fence
on the legs, full in length, turned to the unmanned on-side ring, Bravo runs to make the stop.
The mid-off is deep, pushed straight to him and off they run for a comfortable single.
Haddin attempts to cut loose. Doesn't quite succeed though. He heaves at a fullish delivery on the stumps, ends up dragging it to deep midwicket
attempted yorker, on the middle and leg stump line, dug out to mid-on - again standing deep - and they get a run
fullish, just outside the off stump, steered to the third-man region
from around the sticks, fullish on the off and middle stump line, square-driven to sweeper cover
a length delivery on the off stump line, pushed to mid-off
just outside the off stump line, the ball gripped the surface and almost came in like a off-break, Haddin pushes at it, gets an inside-edge that takes the ball to fine-leg
fullish outside the offstump, driven inside-out past cover
fullish on the off and middle stump, hint of late swing, Haddin drives it towards mid-off
on the leg and middle, Haddin turns it to the on side and will retain the strike
poor delivery, down the leg side, Haddin cashes in, runs it down to the fine-leg fence
better this time. on the stumps, defended watchfully on the off stump.

wonderful wonderful shot. It was a length delivery, just outside the off stump, not much room mind you, opens the blade, waits for the ball to arrive, and late-cuts it past the keeper's gloves! Ala Arjuna Ranatunga!
pushed to covers
hmm... widish delivery, full in length, outside the off stump, Hussey reaches out for it but fails to put bat on ball and Baugh gathers it smartly
Another slower one, this one lands outside the off stump, holds the line and Haddin is beaten as he attempts to square-drive it
length-delivery on the off and middle, pushed back to the bowler
overpitched on the middle and leg, driven down the ground, to long-on
half-volley well outside the off stump, Hussey creams it past cover but finds the sweeper.
yet another slower one, dips outside the offstump, Haddin spots it, adjusts, pushes it to left of point and they take a run
another slower ball, loops in from just outside the off stump - delivered from round the stumps, Hussey lunges forward, is slightly beaten by the change in pace but ends up pushing it to midwicket
fuller one outside the off stump, swatted past cover
short of length, outside the off stump, punched to midwicket
attempted yorker turns into a low full-toss, pushed to cover
Smith keeps the pressure on. Another dot ball. fullish, on the middle and leg, Haddin tries to heave, doesn't find his timing, the ball rolls to midwicket
overpitched on the middle and leg, driven down the ground
Oh! Just short of driveable length, outside the off stump, Hussey goes for a square-drive, gets an edge and the ball flies through the vacant slip region, out to the third-man fence.
defended to midwicket
on off stump, played back to the bowler on the front foot
run down to short third man
slips down leg side, called wide
defended to midiwcket
cut off the back foot past point
short in length and outside off stump, Hussey goes back to cut but hits it to cover
defended back to the bowler
played with an open face past point for one
fired in flat and fast, driven to long on for one
fifty for Hussey, short and outside off stump, glided to third man for four. Well played!
closer to the stumps this tiime, Hussey tries to run it down to third man again but gets beaten
full on off stump, Haddin steps down and drives to long on for one
slower through the air on off stump, dabbed to short third man for a single
tossed up slower thrhough the air, sriven down the ground for one
shorter in length on off stump, dabbed short of cover for one, that was a risky run but the throw to the bowler's end was poor
defended to midwicket on the front foot
outside off stump, played with an open face to short third man
defended on the front foot to point, the batsmen steal one
Haddin breaks the shackles! Tossed up outside off stump, Haddin uses his feet, gets down the track and lofts over midwicket for six
defended on the leg side
fired into the blockhole, dug out on the off side for one
flat and fast on off stump, defended to point
slower throuhg the air on off stump, pushed on the front foot to cover
tossed up on off stump, Haddin steps down and plays it off his pads to midwicket
defended back to the bowler
six more! Carbon copy of the earlier one, steps down the pitch and swings it over the midwicket fence
worked down the fine leg for two
tossed up on off stump, Haddin takes a step down and defends
another six! straight down the ground this time. Haddin is using his feet superbly and he just powered that over the fence
run down to third man
fired in outside off stump, Haddin tries to run it down to third man again but misses, the ball goes past the keeper for a bye
played down the ground to long off for one
full on off stump, flicked off the pads but straight to square leg
tossed up on middle and off stump, dropped short of the cover fielder for a sharp run
full on off stump, played down the ground for another single
full outside off stump, played past point on the front foot
angling into off stump, played with an angled bat behind point for one
comes down the track and pushes it to mid-on
full and outside off stump, Haddin tries to squeeze it past point but doesn't connect
full and outside off stump, Hussey tries to force it through the off side but gets an inside edge back to the bowler
full and wide outside off stump, that was the attempted slower ball, wide called
much closer to the stumps this time, dug out to point on the front foot
cracked through the off side for four! That was short and wide and Hussey cuts it off the front foot past point for four. That brings up Australia's 200
outside off stump, played with an open face behind square on the off side for one
full and drifting into Haddin's pads, flicked to midwicket
short of a length outside off stump and that cut back in a long way, the ball goes past Haddin's inside edge and was so close to the stumps
full outside off stump, Hussey reverse paddles it to third man
full and straight, driven back to Gayle
Haddin brings up his first one-day fifty with a six! Short outside leg stump, Haddin makes room and pulls it over the deep backward square leg fence
in the blockhole, squeezed past point for one
Hussey reverse sweeps from outside off stump again, this time he connects perfectly down to the third man fence for four
full and down leg side, flicked but the ball finds the short fine leg fielder
full and swinging into the pads, flicked to deep midwicket for one
full and wide outside off stump, Hussey reaches out and drives through cover, the fielder in the deep was a bit tardy and the batsmen capitalise and run two

Haddin was nearly run-out! The ball hit Hussey on the pad and rolled on the leg side, Haddin took off but Hussey said no, Taylor picks up, turns but doesn't hit the stumps or Haddin would have been out
cut to cover off the front foot
middle and leg stump line, there's no room on offer and Hussey nudges it to mid-off for one
short and wide outside off stump, Haddin runs it down to third man
creamed through cover for four! That was far too full and there was width outside the off stump as well, Haddin leans into it and cover drives beautifully
worked off the pads to square leg for one
short of a length and angles into Hussey who charges down the track, the angle cramps him for room and he gets hit on the glove for a single to point
wide outside off stump, played to cover for a single
full toss outside off stump, that was the attempted yorker, Hussey drives it to deep cover and the batsmen are lightening quick between the stumps. They manage two
played off the front foot for a single to cover
pulled to deep square leg for one
full and straight in the block hole, perfect ball for the slog overs, Haddin digs it out for a single on the off side
flat ball on the stumps and Hussey goes down on one knee and slog-sweeps it over the midwicket fence
Hussey gives Gayle the charge, fired into his legs, played back to the bowler
Hussey uses his feet again to step down and drive it to long-off
cross-batted swat down to long on for one
wide outside off stump, Haddin tries to run it down to third man but can't connect
slower ball on off stump, Haddin picks it and plays it with an open face for a single to point
what happened there! short of a length and a slower ball to boot, Hussey goes down on one knee and tries to paddle it to square leg, the ball bounces over his head
whack! Hussey backs away and hammers it straight down the ground and over the fence, he moves into the nineties and this is his highest ODI score
in the blockhole, dug out to the bowler
slower ball on the stumps, Hussey lofts it down the ground but doesn't time it well enough for it to reach the fence
full and angling into the pads, Haddin tries to swing it away on the leg side but the ball hits the pad for a leg bye.
loose delivery and duly smashed for four. That was a juicy toss and Hussey pulls it through midwicket for four
hundred for Hussey, drifting down leg side, Hussey backs away and turns it off his pads down to the fine leg fence
played to wide mod-off for one
another one sails over the fence, just short of a length and Hussey swivels and pulls it over the fence at deep backward square leg
short and wide outside off stump, Haddin throws everything behind the heave that was intended to go over the off side, he gets a thick edge down to the third man fence
attempted slower yorker, just outside off stump, Haddin fails to make contact
cheeky, too cheeky for his own good. The slower ball was outside off stump and Haddin moves across and tries to chip it over the wicketkeeper, instead he lobs it straight to short fine leg
the perfect yorker for such a situtation, Hussey could do no more than back away and dig it out to point for a single
another slower ball and it's a full toss, played to midwicket for a single
slower ball outside leg stump, Hussey comes down the track and backs away, he wanted to bash that over the leg side but ends up paddling it to short fine leg

inn2.comm: Full, swinging in late, on the off stump, Gayle stands and nearly delivers. He drives it powerfully but straight to the mid-off fielder
beaten! slightly short of driveable length and just outside the off stump. Gayle has a stab at it, misses.
fast and straight on the middle and leg, pushed to midwicket
West Indies are away and in style. Fullish delivery outside the off stump, Gayle nonchalantly square-drives it past point
short and outside the off stump, inviting Gayle to slash and he does. upper-cuts it over point and to the left of the third-man.
a gentle outswinger, there was bit of width outside the off stump but Gayle decides to let it sail by
first wide of the innings. Down the leg side.
yet to find his radar. This one swings well outside the off stump and, surprisingly, Gayle decides to let it go
Another wide, losing control of that outswinger. Starts off from outside the off stump and veers further away.
hit the deck around the off stump, on a length, Gayle tries to force it off the back foot, doesn't get any power behind the stroke
Landed on a length, just outside the off stump and left Gayle who was squared-up as he tried to defend, gets an outside edge that takes the ball down to the third-man region
Buzzes in that channel outside the off stump, Chanderpaul lets it go through to Haddin
short of length, outside the off stump, punched to cover
a length-delivery on the middle and off stump line, leaving the batsman, Gayle is once again squared-up a bit, but manages to push it towards cover
banged in short, Gayle shapes to pull it away but it was well outside the off stump and only gets an bottom-edge to it. The ball rolls down to the third-man region.
slanted across Chanderpaul, fullish in length. Chanders gets across, covers his stumps and shoulders arms
another one sails into Haddin's gloves.
And again. Lee is hitting the right line and length here, Chanderpaul has been cautious so far.
Deja-vu.  Tight two overs from Lee.
a nip-backer from just outside the off stump, Gayle is hurried in his stroke, gets an inside-edge onto his pads

slightly short and outside the off stump, width was there for Gayle to free his arms. He tried but the ball stopped on him on this wicket with invariable bounce. Just managed to swat it away towards cover point
this one was on the stumps, pushed to the on side
in the channel outside the off stump, Gayle shoulders arms
sails past harmlessly outside the off stump, into Haddin's gloves.
Umpire extends his arms. down the leg side this time.
fullish delivery, just outside the off stump, Gayle puts his right foot out, sees there is no movement in, lets it go through to Haddin
Finally Chanderpaul is tempted. Through the previous over, he had left everything sail past his stumps, but not this time. He poked at a delivery slanting away and is beaten.
lunges forward to a length-delivery and pushes to cover

Chanderpaul, the first-match hero for West Indies, is gone! Umpire Asad Rauf withhelds the appeal after a delay. It was a full-length delivery, slanting away outside the off stump, Chanderpaul lunges at it, has a poke and is beaten. The ball appeared to have brushed his back-pad enroute to Haddin, who dived low to his left to take it. but did it touch the bat. Shall report after I get a good look at the replays.
fullish on the middle and off, pushed to the off side
a length delivery, just outside the off stump, Sarwan hops back and attempts to force it away, the bat comes down in an angle and all he gets is an inside edge...
Lovely yorker! fast, flat and straight at the off stump, Sarwan gets his bat down in time
Fullish on the off stump line, patted out towards cover
No patting this time. Gayle unleashes a powerful off-drive but Katich, at mid-off, dives to his right to make a good stop.
slightly short of a length, Gayle hangs back and cuts fiercely but straight to cover
length delivery, on the off and middle stump line, this one came in with the angle. Gayle opens up in his stance, pushes it to midwicket
length-delivery, on the off and middle stump line, kept a touch low, Gayle retreats back into the crease and keeps it out
slips in a slower one. Dips in front of the middle stump, Gayle pushes it towards mid-on and will retain the strike
hit the deck short of length, just outside the leg stump line and it came in towards leg , Gayle swivels to jab it away to fine-leg
lovely skilful shot. It was banged in short, outside the off stump and it kicked up. Sarwan stayed beside the line, let the ball climb and gently helped it to sail over the slips.
slash and a miss. Length delivery outside the off stump, Sarwan gets excited at the room and throws his bat at it, doesn't connect.
another length-delivery, landed just outside the off stump and came in off the seam. Sarwan hops back and pushes it back down the track
length-ball that kicked up, around the off stump line and Sarwan hops up and back again, and pushes it to cover point
fullish delivery, slanting away, Sarwan presses forward and drives but doesn't find his timing and the ball rolls to the right of mid-on
fullish on  the off stump line, Gayle gets behind it and pushes it towards mid-off
slanting away after landing on a length, Sarwan tries to force it away, bat comes down in an angle, and a inside-edge results that takes the ball to the on side
slower one, on the middle and off stump line. Sarwan spots it , lunges forward to present the full face of the bat in defense
overpitched on the middle and off, Sarwan drives inside-out to the left of mid-off
fullish on the middle and leg, Gayle pushes at it, gets an inside-edge on to his pads
half-volley on the off stump line, should have been put away, but Sarwan drills it straight to mid-off
fullish on the middle stump line, Sarwan gets his bat around his pads, tickles it behind square-leg
Lee slips in a slower delivery, outside the off stump, Sarwan waits for the ball to arrive, opens the face of the bat to send the ball down to third-man
banged in short on the leg and middle stump line, slanting across Gayle, who is a bit surprised by the extra bounce but manages to steer it to third-man
just short of driveable-length, on the middle stump, Sarwan again plays around his pads, tucks it to square-leg
length delivery, on the off and middle, driven to mid-on
Lovely off-drive. In the slot outside the off stump, Sarwan goes through the line and the ball speds past the diving mid-off fielder
right up there in the blockhole, on the off stump, Gayle gets into a tangle, loses his balance, pushes at it and gets an inside edge...
outside the off stump, room and length to tap it away to third man
angled across, Sarwan wants to run it down to third-man, misses.
overpitched outside the off stump,  driven straight to short-cover.
slower ball, on the off stump line, driven to the off side.
punched towards mid-off
tries to hit the deck on the off stump line, Gayle wants to pull it away but doesn't get much power behind it.
outside the off stump, fullish in length, run down to third-man
slashed over slips. It was a length delivery, outside the off stump, Sarwan eased back and upper cut it over slips.
on the stumps, pushed to the cover
that one jagged back in sharply. A perfect nip-backer, Sarwan has a stab at it, gets an inside edge
short of length, outside the off stump, run down to third-man
Super shot. full and outside the off stump, Sarwan went back a bit and creamed it, inside-out, between mid-off and cover. Great shot.
thwack! Bracken slips in a slower ball but Sarwan was not decieved. He waited for it, took his left out outside the line, and smoked it inside-out past extra cover.

Length-delivery, in the channel outside the off stump, Sarwan shapes to cut, but is cramped. Just before the bat comes down the ball squeezes through,  hits the flap of the back pad, the bat now comes down and thuds into the pad, and Haddin takes it. did the ball touch the glove enroute? The umpire definitely thinks so, replays are not too conclusive.
pushed to cover
beaten on the forward prod by a length-delivery slanting across.
low full-toss on the off stump, Gayle, surprisingly, just pats it to cover point
on the leg and middle, Gayle presses forward and the ball holds its line, and Gayle just pushes it back down the track
Whack! Banged in short, on the off stump line and Gayle murders it over midwicket. Pulled powerfully.
hits the length this time and Gayle respects it by dead-batting to the off side
pushed across outside the off stump, Gayle wants to drill it away, throws his bat at it but doesn't connect.
short of length, outside the off stump, steered to third-man region
wide down the leg side.
Aha! The famous whiplash square-drive is out for viewing pleasure. Fullish, outside the off stump, Lara gets on to it quickly and whips it past point.
Fuller one on the stumps but Lara decides to send it past midwicket. He leans forward, works his wrists over time and turns it to the on side. Finally, the over ends.
pushed to the off side, Gayle wants a run, Lara, wisely, doesn't.
on the middle and leg, Gayle works it, around his front pad, to the on side

Low flat full-toss on the legs, Gayle attempts unsuccessfully to flick and it runs off the pads to the fine-leg fence. The west Indian duo, surprisingly, don't run hard, think it would be a boundary and just jog through. But Stuart Clarke had made the stop and only one run resulted.
Orgasmic straight drive! It was a length ball, just outside the off stump, Lara glides forward, and drives it through the line, past the bowler, past the hapless mid-off and into the fence.
well outside the off stump, Lara thrusts his front pad out, and lets it go through to Haddin.
Thwack! it was a length ball outside the off stump, Gayle backs away and swings it over mid-on
Almost murdered the bowler! It was a low full-toss and Gayle freed his arms and how. The ball whizzed past the surprised, nay, shocked bowler and crashed into the long-on fence.
short of length delivery, outside the off stump, steered behind point

Gayle show is definitely on. Predetermined assault is on. Short of length delivery, just outside the off stump mind you, but Gayle backs away to the leg side, and upper cuts it over backward point. The white ball is flying everywhere!
overpitched outside the off stump, Gayle stood there and delivered regally. High back-lift and the bat comes down hard on the ball and it screams past the hapless diving mid-off fielder.
length delivery on the off stump line, Gayle drives to cover
pitches on leg stump, Lara gets across and whips it down to fine leg
poor ball, wide outside leg stump, Gayle gets slightly across and helps it down to the fine-leg fence
better line, just outside off stump, Gayle prods forward and gets a thick outside edge down to third man
full on off stump, Lara drives on the front foot to cover

Lara escapes being run-out by the skin of his teeth, that ball was on middle and leg stump, Lara riskily got across his stumps and flicked it to deep square leg, Lara wants the second and Lee fires the throw in to Haddin, Lara was millimetres over the line when the bails came off
worked off his pads past square leg
picthes outside of stump and moves away, Lara lets it go
pitches outside off stump and skids on to Lara's angled bat, played to point
short of a length outside off stump, glided down to third man
full and straight, driven to long-on for one
middle and off stump line, Lara moves across and drives it through midwicket for four, delightful shot!
outside off stump line, Lara opens theface and glances it to third man
defended on the leg side
full and straight, played with a straight bat back to the bowler
leg and middle stump line, just short of a length, Lara jumps across and plays it off his hips down to fine leg
slower ball outside off stump and it moves away from Gayle who tries to play it down to third man, he was beaten by the change of pace
full and on off stump, Gayle stands tall and biffs it down the ground
short of a length outside off stump, Lara drives through the line but hits it straight to mid-off
angling across Gayle from middle and leg stump, played with an angled bat down to third man for one
straighter line this time on off and middle stump, Lara still runs it down to third man
full and straight, driven down the ground
full outside off stump, Lara reaches out and drives to deep cover
short of a length, driven on the front foot to deep cover, that's Gayle's fifty, his second of the tournament
outside off stump and short of a length, lofted over covers but there's a fielder in the deep
full on middle and leg stump, Lara closes the face of the bat a touch too early while trying to flick and gets a leading edge that falls just short of point
good length on off stump, defended on the off side
excellent ball, pitched on middle stumpa nd moved a shade away from Lara who tried to defend on the front foot but was comprehensivley beaten. Haven't seen that in a while!
drifting down leg side, the ball hits the pad and runs down to fine leg for one
full and wide outside off stump, Gayle throws his bat and it but doesn't time it well enough, he gets a single down to long-off
full on off stump and that swung back in to Lara who got half forward and inside edges it on to his pad
short of a length om middle and off stump, Gayle stands up and drives off the back foot to long-off
fuller length on off stump, Lara drives on the front foot but finds cover
full ball on the pads, Lara gets across and dispatches it through square leg
wide outside off stump this time, cut down to third man for another single
slower ball just outside off stump, Gayle initially started to play at it but pulled out of the shot
worked off the pads to square leg
pitches outside off stump and shapes into Lara who waits for it and runs it off the face of his bat down to third man
full and on middle and leg stump, Gayle flicks but hussey dives across from midwicket and cuts it off, the batsmen decide against what would have been a risky run
short outside off stump, Gayle cuts hard off the back foot, sweeper does the fielding
good length ball and straight, Lara gets on the front foot and defends
tight line on off stump, absolutely no room to work it on either side of the wicket, defended on the front foot
a touch shorter in length but straight as an arrow, Lara goes back, covers his stumps and blocks
short of a length, pitches outside leg and spins across Gayle who gets hit on the pad
fuller this time outside leg stump, Gayle tries to flick it but closes the face too early, he gets a leading edge on the off side
defended back to the bowler
pitches outside leg stump and hits Lara on the pad
and again, spinning across Lara from outside leg stump, the batsman plays forward but is hit on the pad
worked off the pads to midwicket for one
good line on off stump, defended on the leg side
pitches on middle and moves a shade away from Lara who gets squared up and edges it down to third man for a single
a touch slower this time, good length on off stump, defended on the front foot towards cover
just short of a length, pitches on leg and middle and hits Lara high on the thigh, he wants a leg bye but Gayle sends him back
a touch wide outside off stump this time, Lara slaps it to deep cover
pushed to mid-on
short of a length outside leg stump, Lara steps down but doesn't get to the pitch of the ball, so he defends
wide outside leg stump, Lara tries to sweep but misses, wide called
another wide down leg side, Lara tried to sweep again
Lara uses his feet, steps down and backs away to make room and flicks it through midwicket for two
Lara steps down again and backs away to make room, Cullen drops it short so Lara chops it wide of the short fine leg for four
and again, this time he runs it fine between short fine leg and the keeper for four more
Lara comes down the track again but defends to the bowler
outside leg stump, swept down to deep fine leg for a single
forced off the back foot to midwicket
angling into Gayle from round the wicket, just outside off stump and Gayle chops it down to third man
good length delivery on middle stump, that bounced more than Lara expected and hurried him, the ball hits the glove and goes to square leg
played to point
full and angling into the pads, flicked off the toes through square leg
a touch wide outside off stump and Lara drives it sweetly through cover to bring up the 100-run partnership
airy drive goes just wide of the fielder at cover, Hayden runs around and saves the boundary
tossed up on middle stump, Gayle waits for it and plays it late with and open face to short third man
nudged in front of point and they scamper through for a single, Lara brings up his fifty, well played
drifts down leg side, wide called
driven down to long-on for one
short of a length outside leg stump, Gayle goes back and gets hit on the pad
angling into Lara from round the wicket, defended to point on the front foot
driven on the front foot, Symonds misfields at cover to allow the single
outside off stump, Lara moves across and flicks it past midwicket for four
run down to third man with an open face for a single
straight ball defended back to the bowler
played to third man for another single
full and angling into Gayle from round the wicket, the batsmen goes back and defends on the off side
short and outside off stump, that kept a touch low, Gayle cuts hard off the back foot but can't beat the fielder at point
good length and homing into off and middle stump, defended to cover
played off the pads to short fine leg
full and on the pads again, defended to midwicket
short of a length outside off stump, Gayle squares up and runs it down to third man
whack! Clark tosses up an easy full toss and Gayle bludgeons it back over his head for six
sprays it wide down leg side, Haddin fumbles the take and the batsmen cash in, wide called
oh my, an inside edge goes past the stumps and beats Haddin as well as it runs down to the fence. Lara tried to smash that down the ground but got in all sorts of trouble
this time he makes room and comes down the pitch and drives powerfully past mid-on for four more
pulled to short midwicket
dropped at mid-on but it was a no-ball anyway! Lara lofted it straight to Cullen at mid-on but the ball bounces off his palms.
drifts down leg side, the ball hits the pad and goes to short fine leg
another no-ball and it was sprayed down leg side as well, Clark is having a horrendous night
this time he doesn't over step but he still sprays it down leg side, wide called
oh my, he oversteps yet again and drifts on to the pads, worked down to fine leg
played past point for one, that's the end of an 11-ball over
dug in short and angling into Gayle's body, he stands up tall and fends it down the leg side
angling into the batsman from round the wicket, played to midwicket
full and on the pads, Gayle flicks off his toes for four to square leg, West indies are running away with it here
biffed down the ground for four! Short of a length and Gayle hits through the line for four more
defended to mid-on
pushed to mid-on again, this time the batsmen manage to run a sharp single
and he strikes right away, short ball and Gayle pulls it straight to midwicket. Usually he would have sent that miles over the fence but he mis-timed it this time and found Hussey
banged it short outside off stump but it doesn't bounce that much, Bravo swerves out of the way
tight line just outside off stump, played to point on the back foot
wider outside the off stump and Bravo watchfully lets it go
on middle and off stump and it keeps low, Bravo defends on the back foot
sprayed wide outside off stump and it moves further away from Bravo
left alone outside off stump
full and angling into off stump, defended on the off side
angling into middle from outside off stump, Lara moves across his stumps and whips it to deep square leg
full and straight, Bravo defends back to Lee who picks it up and pretends to fire it back at the batsman
slanting into middle and leg stump, worked off the pads to midwicket
full toss on the pads, flicked down to deep midwicket for two
defended back to the bowler
short of a length and pitches outside leg stump, Lara moves across and gets hit on the pad, the Australians appeal for leg before but in vain. West indies bring up the 200
left alone outside off stump
good length, slanting into Bravo's off and middle stumps, defended on the front foot
poor delivery, pitches very wide outside off stump and moves further away
full outside off stump, Bravo gets forward and drives, he doesn't time it well but finds the gap between extra cover and mid-off
straight ball on middle stump, worked off the pads through midwicket
slanting across Lara who opens the face and tries to run it past the fielder at point who dives across to make a superb save
fullish length on middle stump, flicked to square leg
tossed up outside off stump, Bravo has a swish t it but misses
flatter through the air on off stump, defended on the back foot
tossed up outside off stump, Bravo half-heartedly goes forward and pokes at it, gets hit on the pad
turned to midwicket on the front foot
tossed up on off stump, defended on the front foot
Pushed to midwicket
Banged in short, and it climbed more than what Lara expected, he half-shut his eye, and used his wrist to keep his pull down
down the leg side, brushes the pad enroute to Haddin
fullish, pushed to cover
just short of driveable length around the off stump line, pushed towards mid-off
floated outside the legstump, Lara dances  down the track, gets beside the line, and drives to long-on
Bravo comes down the track this time, drives, mis-times, gets an outside edge past point
Wow! crashes into the sightscreen. tossed up on the leg and middle stump line, Lara comes down the track, doesn't reach the pitch of the ball but still decides to go through the line.
tries to repeat, but Cullen drags back the length and pushes it outside off, Lara adjusts, checks his shot, pushes at it in a defensive mode
almost a run-out. Lara tries to sweep, misses, the ball runs off the pads towards point, there was a shy at Lara's end, if it had hit , Lara would have been history
defended off the front foot
slower ball, Bravo spots it, leans forward, drives inside-out but straight to cover

Watson spits at the top of his run-mark. Runs in to bowl and oh ho could have got Bravo. It was a bouncer and Bravo goes for a brave hook, gets a top-edge, the ball ballons over the keeper's head, Haddin gives the pursuit but the ball carries too far for him.
fullish, just outside the off stump, Bravo pushes at it, and the ball runs down to third-man
a length-delivery on the legs, Lara gets inside the line, tickles it fine to the fine-leg fence. A cry of anguish erupts from Watson.
tries to run it down to third man and is beaten
on the middle stump, Bravo leans forward and turns it past midwicket
fullish outside off, square-driven to sweeper cover
just outside the off stump, patted towards short third-man region and they hurry through for a quicksingle
fullish outside off, tries to square-drive, gets an outside edge which takes the ball past backward point
outside the off stump, tries to square-drive, gets beaten
length-delivery outside the off stump, Bravo steers it , deliberately, through the vacant slip region. Watson has a few words to say to Bravo!
Wide down the leg side and Haddin doesn't manage to stop it cleanly
speared one on the legs, Lara tries to flick it away, doesn't connect and it runs off the pads behind square-leg
Slower ball, on the hips, Bravo waits, turns it behind square and they run hard to take two
short of length outside the off stump, steered to third-man region
short of length outside the off stump, Lara goes for a slash, top-hand comes off the bat-handle and ball flies over the slip region

Length delivery just outside the off stump, Bravo shuffles across, pats it close to the off side and by the time Symonds comes in from cover, and has a shy at the non-striker's end (backed by Watson at mid-on) the players are through.
Lee gets Lara! Banged in short, Lara went for a pull, the ball stopped on him, he was through his stroke, and the ball hit the back of the bat and popped up to short fine-leg
on the legs, tucked past square-leg
slower ball, 74.4 mph delivery, full and on the middle and leg, Bravo plays a lovely pick-up shot , ala Carl Hooper, over midwicket
speared in full and fast on the legs, tries to flick it away, doesn't connect and the ball thuds into the pad.
slanted across Hinds, who watches it carefully and allows that one to go through to Haddin.
short of length, just outside the off stump, Hinds cuts but straight to point.
wide one outside the off stump, and it goes one-bounce to Haddin
another one outside the off stump, Hinds goes for a cut, but is beaten by the lack of bounce. The ball sails under the bat, through to Haddin.
short of length, outside the off stump, Hinds, again, goes for a cut, mistimes it and the ball rolls to point
length delivery on the off stump line, Hinds goes back and punches it back to the bowler
half-volley outside the off stump, Hinds reaches out for it, square-drives but straight to point
full and fast, Bravo drove it back down the track, Lee stretches out his left foot, the ball canons into his boots and they go through for a single
bouncer.... reared up throat high, just over the off stump line, Hinds drops his wrists and sways out of the way

gone! West Indian fans might be fearing the onset of yet another calypso collapso. Fullish delivery , outside the off stump, Hinds goes for his bottom-hand powered drive, just manages to get a edge and Haddin does the rest. Australia are slowing trying to fight thier way back. But with Samuels walking out and Dwayne Smith and Baugh still in , West Indies should wrap this up but ....
yorker first up. This is Lee's last over and he is giving it all. Samuels is upto it though, gets his bat down in time

Oh my god! West Indies have contrived a run-out. Samuels turns one to point, he wants a non-existent run, sent back by Bravo and Michael Clarke doesn't miss. Samuels had not gone too far across but far enough to not be able to turn back in time.
Right up there, fullish delivery, driven to cover

oh ho! Dwayne Smith announces himself with a spanking pull. This was Lee's last ball of the match and Smith was in no mood to see him off. Bravado or fool-hardiness? Take your pick. But it was there to be hit and he did exactly that.
driven back, Symonds get a touch and it crashes into the stumps at the other end. but Bravo was inside his crease. No harm done!
pushed to cover
on the legs, turned to square-leg

Another one goes. And then they were three. Tossed up slow, on the off stump line, turned in, Smith leans forward, and tries to work it across to the on side, misses, and the ball hits the pads before going on to disturb the furniture.
goes for a drive outside the off stump, misses
oh ho! almost a mis-understanding. Driven to cover, Baugh wants a run but luckily, Bravo wisely, sends him back
fullish on the middle and leg stump line, Bravo presses forward, pushes it down the ground, to long-on
length-delivery slanting across, Baugh shuffles across, gets behind the line, pushes it towards cover
overpitched outside the off stump, Baugh drives it straight to cover
short of length, outside the off stump and this one kept very low and Baugh jumps across his stumps, pokes at it and misses.
Baugh tries to get out but fails! fullish outside the off stump, he goes for an extravagant square-drive, misses
pushed to right of point
Baugh breaks free. It was tossed up outside the off stump, overpitched and Baugh frees his arms and sends the ball crashing into the cover fence. Surely  West Indies can't lose now?
on the legs, turned behind square-leg
outside the off stump, driven to the sweeper cover
on the off stump line, turns in slightly, Bravo goes back and dead-bats it away
pushed to the covers and wants a run, Bravo, again shows a cool head, sends him back.
outside the off stump, Baugh shapes as if he is about to throw his bat at it, but decides against it.
defended off the back foot
low full-toss, on the off stump line, driven inside-out to the left of mid-off, manned by Katich,

Take that! Awesome shot over long-off.  Slower one, fullish outside the off stump, Bravo leans forward and goes through the line of the ball, top-hand comes off the bat-handle and West Indies now need only two runs.
turned in the air towards square-leg
defended off the front foot

Bravo dances down the track, reaches the pitch of the ball, drives it to mid-on and before the throw comes in, they cross over for the matchwinning single. West Indies win by three wickets and they are almost ensured of a place in the finals.
